p2
VScholarly recital
p3
sVnews
p4
VKalabharathi recently witnessed a vocal recital that tugged at the heartstrings of audience. The vocalist who kept listeners spellbound for about two hours was Mahamahopadhyay Nookala China Satyanarayana from Hyderabad, who was chosen to be adorned with the national honour, the Padma Bhushan. The soulful and scholarly presentation was for the Andhra Music Academy at its 10th annual festival of music and dance.At the fete, which was inaugurated by VPT chairman Ajeya Kallam, IAS, in the auspicious presence of Sadguru K. Sivananda Murty, Nookala was felicitated and honoured by the Sangeetha Kalanidhi Nedunuri Krishnamurty, president of the Academy, former DGP R. Prabhakar Rao, IPS, vice-president and great patron of fine arts B. Madhav Rao, secretary P.V.S. Seshai Sastry and presidents of almost all Sangeetha sabhas like VMDA and VMA.The octogenarian vocalist (disciple of Dwaram Venkataswamy Naidu and Sreepada Pinakapani) and revered guru who has authored many books on Carnatic music, was accompanied by noted violinist M. Surya Deepthi (staffer, AIR, Hyderabad) and renowned mridangam player V.V. Ramanamurty (staffer AIR, Visakhapatnam). Starting with Begada for Vallabha Nayakascha, he next aptly chose to sing Guruleka (Gourimanohari) and Yenatinomu phalamo successively with elaborate alapana, neravu and swaram.He concluded rendering a slokam in ragamalika (Behag, Kapi and Sindhubhairavi) and his own thillana in Sindhubhairavi. Both Surya Deepthi and Ramanamurty successfully enhanced the splendour that was surfaced by Nookala.
